rComments: Loved the class. Loved the prof.
One of the best professors I have ever had.

This course was Environmental Politics in Canada; if you find that material interesting, you'll love this course.  Prof Olive lectures were captivating and she would often bring up the latest news in politics and what nations are doing globally about climate change. For papers and tests, you rally have to think critically and form strong arguments.

Enjoyed this course. Lectures were interesting and not very long. There was a focus on group discussions, through an online forum each week, which made up a good part of your mark. I recommend going over the rubric for these so you do well from the beginning. Material isn't hard, some reading required. Only 2 major assignments, not research based.

I really liked Prof. Olive. She didn't spend a lot of time lecturing, majority of the time is spent in discussion groups. A lot of group work. A lot of reports, week after week, but these are individual. Group presentation. Course load is heavy but the material isn't hard. A lot of research is required for reports. Some reading required.
